list.abstract: actually（英 [ˈæktʃuəli]，美 [ˈæktʃuəli]），英语单词，副词，意思为事实上；实际上；竟然。短语搭配有actually mean（实际意思）。例句为“I actually began to build up my arm muscles shaking my set.（事实上，我开始通过甩动装备来增强我的手臂肌肉。）” actually副词类近义词有really、effectively、virtually等，名词形式为actualization、actuality。

yingyinNormal.zh: 实际上，我们已经找到合我们心意的房子了。

yingyinNormal.zh: 实际上我在琢磨我能不能再加一个新的棋子。

yingyinNormal.en: Actually, I thought the first two renditions were far more compelling.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实际上，我觉得前两个版本要吸引人得多。

yingyinNormal.en: What are you doing in the girls' hall? I was actually looking for you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在女生楼里干嘛呢？实际上，我在找你。

yingyinNormal.en: Actually, it's some stuff you left at my apartment. Well, thanks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实际上，这些是你落在我公寓的。噢，噢，谢谢。

yingyinNormal.en: Team. But I'm here alone. Actually, I'm here to sing with her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 队伍，但我是一个人。实际上，我来这里和她唱的。

yingyinNormal.en: Will you tell him he's out of his mind. Actually, I get what he's saying.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你告诉他吧，他疯了。实际上，我能理解他。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, actually, it's a really long story. I... Oh, well, it's him. Hey, hold on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实际上，说来话长，我是他的…电话，等等。

yingyinNormal.en: What? You can't know that. Nobody can. But I do know that, actually.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么？这您可说不准。没人能说准，但实际上我就能。

yingyinNormal.en: Pancakes, yay! Oh, we're actually out of those. You can have the rest.
yingyinNormal.zh: 煎饼，好棒！实际上家里没有煎饼了。你可以吃剩下的。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, it's more of an anniversary. The 30th anniversary of our game, actually.
yingyinNormal.zh: 只是周年庆典啦，实际上是我们游戏30周年纪念。

yingyinNormal.en: Actually, do you mind driving? I don't technically have a license. Sure.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实际上，你介意你开车吗？严格来说我没有驾照。可以。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, same old, same old. Actually, I'm glad I'm running into you like this.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道的，老样子，实际上，这个时候遇到你我很高兴。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Actually</highlight> it was surprisingly affordable.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 实际上，它的价格惊人的实惠。

examination_example.sentence: However, you don't have to <highlight>actually</highlight> be alone to feel that way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，你并不一定要独处才能有这种(孤独的)感觉。

examination_example.sentence: In contrast, being alone can <highlight>actually</highlight> be a blessing, particularly when you've actively chosen it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，独处实际上是一种福气，尤其是当你主动选择独处的时候。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Actually</highlight>, it's the beginning of next month for the job.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 实际上，这是下个月初的工作。

examination_example.sentence: Chances are you've <highlight>actually</highlight> seen this place.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你很有可能见过这个地方。

examination_example.sentence: The students were <highlight>actually</highlight> very positive about the experience.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，学生们对这次体验的评价都非常积极。

examination_example.sentence: I'm feeling rather sad, <highlight>actually</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 实际上，我感到很难过。

examination_example.sentence: I'm so happy to be <highlight>actually</highlight> on the road now.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我很高兴现在要真正开车上路了。

examination_example.sentence: They are <highlight>actually</highlight> shorter than their earlier generations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们实际上比其前几代人更矮。

examination_example.sentence: But how many bacteria <highlight>actually</highlight> transfer in five seconds?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是在五秒之内到底有多少细菌转移了呢?

examination_example.sentence: That's how we found the Pearl, <highlight>actually</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 实际上，我们就是那样发现珍珠餐厅的。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Actually</highlight> space technology helps people on earth every day.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，太空技术每天都在帮助地球上的人们。

examination_example.sentence: I've <highlight>actually</highlight> just learned of this concept myself.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其实我自己刚了解到这个概念。

examination_example.sentence: Traffic in the U.S. is <highlight>actually</highlight> getting worse.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国的交通状况实际上越来越糟。

examination_example.sentence: In daily life, forgetting <highlight>actually</highlight> has clear advantages.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在日常生活中，遗忘实际上有着鲜明的优点。

examination_example.sentence: In literacy, they were <highlight>actually</highlight> doing better than their peers in other countries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在读写能力方面，他们(美国大学生)实际上比其他国家的同龄人更优秀。

examination_example.sentence: They are not <highlight>actually</highlight> as safe as automakers advertise.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们(自动驾驶汽车)实际上并不像汽车制造商宣传的那样安全。

examination_example.sentence: It <highlight>actually</highlight> had a very negative effect on morale and performance.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这实际上对士气和绩效有非常不利的影响。

examination_example.sentence: This "once in a lifetime" event <highlight>actually</highlight> may take place twice in some folks' lives.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种“一生一次”的事件实际上有可能在一些人的生活中发生两次。

examination_example.sentence: What makes a game game-like is that the player <highlight>actually</highlight> cares about the outcome.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 游戏之所以像游戏，是因为玩家其实很在乎结果。

examination_example.sentence: You <highlight>actually</highlight> love tipping!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你们实际上很喜欢给小费。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Actually</highlight>, I'm on my way to a job interview.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，我正在去面试的路上。

examination_example.sentence: The mice are not just dealing with the gravity change but <highlight>actually</highlight> seem to be enjoying it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 老鼠不仅能应对重力变化，而且似乎竟还乐在其中。
